// Enemy-bullet configuration — collision radius per bullet kind.
//
// All radii are used for circle-based collision detection.
// The glow-mesh radius in the danmaku spawn helpers also derives from these
// values (full replacement planned for Phase 19 sprites).
//
// | Field               | Unit | Description                                   |
// |---------------------|------|-----------------------------------------------|
// | small_round_radius  | px   | SmallRound — compact circular bullet          |
// | knife_radius        | px   | Knife — thin elongated blade bullet           |
// | rice_radius         | px   | Rice — small oval bullet                      |
// | medium_round_radius | px   | MediumRound — standard circular bullet        |
// | star_radius         | px   | Star — medium star-shaped bullet              |
// | bubble_radius       | px   | Bubble — large translucent circular bullet    |
// | large_round_radius  | px   | LargeRound — large circular bullet            |
EnemyBulletConfig(
    small_round_radius: 4.0,
    knife_radius: 4.0,
    rice_radius: 5.0,
    medium_round_radius: 7.0,
    star_radius: 8.0,
    bubble_radius: 9.0,
    large_round_radius: 11.0,
)
